TASK 1:
       Connect a USB webcam to your computer, install any required drivers, and verify that the webcam works by opening the default camera app and capturing a photo.


USB Webcam Installation and Verification

1. Connected the USB webcam to an available USB port on the computer.
2. Waited for Windows to detect the new hardware.
3. Allowed Windows to automatically install the required drivers.
4. Verified in Device Manager that the webcam appeared under "Cameras" with no warning symbols.
5. Opened the Windows Camera app from the Start menu.
6. Confirmed that the webcam displayed a live video preview.
7. Clicked the Capture button to take a photo.
8. Verified that the photo was saved successfully in the Pictures > Camera Roll folder.

Result:
The USB webcam was detected successfully, the drivers were installed correctly, and the webcam worked properly in the Windows Camera app. A test photo was captured successfully.
